i would prefer to do this in `webpack.config.js`, adding `'babel-polyfill'` to the entry array
https://babeljs.io/docs/usage/polyfill/

``` js
module.exports = {
   entry: ['babel-polyfill', './app/js']
};
```

i think codeclimate is a really useful feature and if `object-rest-spread` operators aren't supported yet, i would be in favor of not using them in caravel at this point. seems like maybe it's a bit too early in the adoption process/not yet standardized. as much as the object-rest-spread operator is a really nice syntax, we can definitely opt out of using it quite easily with `Object.assign`.

here's a good comparison of the two on stack overflow: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/32925460/spread-operator-vs-object-assign

with rest-spread:

``` js
const defaultObj = {
  thing1: 'one',
  thing2: 2,
  thing3: [1,2,3],
};

const mergedObj = {
  ...defaultObj,
  thing4: 'four',
  thing5: [1,2,3,4,5],
};
```

without rest-spread:

``` js
const defaultObj = {
  thing1: 'one',
  thing2: 2,
  thing3: [1,2,3],
};

const newObj = {
  thing4: 'four',
  thing5: [1,2,3,4,5],
};

const mergedObj = Object.assign({}, defaultObj, newObj);
```
